      "body": "Let's ignore the long running times for a moment. This PR is pedantic (and that's good). But I think if we want to be pedantic, then this is the right fix:\n\n```c\n    i = 0;\n    do {\n        secp256k1_rfc6979_hmac_sha256_generate(hash_ctx, &rng, nonce32, 32);\n        i++;\n        if (i == 0) {\n            break;  /* overflow */\n        }\n    } while (i <= counter);\n```\n\nThe `i == 0` could be added to the `while` of course, but I think this one is more readable. \n\n(This is hard to get right; I hope I got it right. :D)",
